The Armed Forces of the Russian Federation is the armed forces of Russia , created after the breakup of the Soviet Union .
The Armed Forces is known to be one of the biggest in the world with about 1,200,000 troops active .
Russia also makes its own weapons .
The Armed Forces has 6 branches : Russian Air Force , Russian Ground Forces , Russian Navy , Strategic Missile Troops , Russian Space Troops and the Russian Airborne Troops .
The current Commander-In-Chief is President Dmitry Medvedev .
When the Soviet Union broke up , Russia was left with nothing .
The country 's president Boris Yeltsin , had to fix Russia and put in a military .
So , Yeltsin appointed himself the Russian minister of defense .
Eventually , CIS helped Russia get it 's defense into shape .
Then in 1993 , a doctrine was made to set up the official military .
As of 2008 , 480,000 men joined the Armed Forces of the Russian Federation .
The term is usually a year .
Russians can join at the age of 18 to 27 years old .
